    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reinstate the government Department for Energy and Climate Change",
        "additional_details": "Over the past few weeks schoolchildren have been on strike and Extinction Rebellion have been peacefully protesting across London. There are millions of us who can see the need for urgent action NOW before the damage becomes irreversible.  \r\n\r\nThis petition calls for the government to resume working full time on these issues rather than relegating them to the background.  We are an amazing, creative and innovative group of people, we in the UK should be at the forefront of this global challenge.",
        "background": "A caller to BBC  Radio 4 Any Answers programme today (April 20th 2019) has challenged climate change protestors to  exhaust \u2018 the proper channels\u2019 before taking to the streets. So, here is a petition calling for the UK government to reinstate the Department for Energy and Climate Change.",
